On Sun, 06 Jun 2004 19:13:37 GMT, Ben Sisson<br />
&lt;ilkhanikeDIESPAM@yahoo.ca&gt; wrote:<br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt;Dear Guild and Community Representatives,<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;Thanks you very much for a great Summit! By all accounts it was a huge<br />
&gt;success. I can speak for the EverQuest Development Team and tell you<br />
&gt;that we're all grateful for the input you provided. In fact, in trying<br />
&gt;to generate this list to give to you this evening, we realized there<br />
&gt;was so much to go over that we wouldn't be able to get a complete list<br />
&gt;togather in time. We're committed to not only listening to your<br />
&gt;feedback, but working with you to make EverQuest more enjoyable for<br />
&gt;yours to come.<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;So, we decided to list the Top Ten themes we would address starting<br />
&gt;Monday, as well as the most common themes that we'll come back with<br />
&gt;more information on by mid-week next week.<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;A quick discussion resulted in a list of items that we will immediatly<br />
&gt;address:<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;-Add scripting to shut off empty instances of Plane of Time<br />
&gt;-Raid message of the day<br />
&gt;-Improving how we handle beta and the testing process<br />
&gt;-Increase the number of debuffs allowed on MOBs<br />
&gt;-Increase buffs on players thru AA's<br />
&gt;-Note field on raid window<br />
&gt;-Improved consent &amp; drag for raid, group and guild<br />
&gt;-Improve corpse drag radius<br />
&gt;-Make charms not no-drop<br />
&gt;-Guild and individual rewards for guild beta testing<br />
&gt;-Work on larger To Do List... I know this is a little random<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;Future items we will immediately begin looking at and discussing are<br />
&gt;as follows:<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;-Plane of Time instancing and other issues<br />
&gt;-back flagging solutions to help with high end guild atrophy<br />
&gt;-Improve raid and guild functionality<br />
&gt;-Auto loot all for your corpse<br />
&gt;-Improvements to Raid XP<br />
&gt;-No more alien NPC's (focusing more on familiar norrathian themes)<br />
&gt;-Solo LDoN-Style instances or similar content<br />
&gt;-Issues with item augmentations<br />
&gt;-Possible enhancement to Guild Wars<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;Of course these aren't all of the itmes. You brought us a CD, 2 Books,<br />
&gt;20 printed sheets of a manifesto. We'll need to go through all of<br />
&gt;those and our notes before we can really get a good tally of all of<br />
&gt;the wonderful ideas and questions that were presented.<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;Thank you again for your feedback and participation. We've had a<br />
&gt;greatd weekend and a wonderful display of things to come.<br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;Sincerely,<br />
&gt;EverQuest Development Team<br />
&gt;</font><br />
