&lt;teapray@realpeopleonly.yahoo.com&gt; wrote:<br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt;Michael Johnson wrote:</font><br />
<font color="#7F7FFF"><br />
&gt;<br />
&gt;   But over all... the #1 thing they list is fixing something with the<br />
&gt;freaking Plane of Time???  Um... I don't think they really get it.</font><br />
<br />
<br />
Speaking from the point of view from someone in a Plane of Time guild,<br />
I am happy to see that they are fixing this. Do I think it should be<br />
the #1 priority for all things in the game? No.<br />
<br />
I can say that unless you have been there, you can't understand the<br />
frustrations that there are with going through all the raids and time<br />
spent to get to Plane of Time, and then having to deal with bug after<br />
bug there, all the while having to be wary of how much time you are in<br />
there for so you don't ruin another guild's instance. Sometimes when<br />
there, I wonder if we're fighting the mobs, or Sony's bugs more. To<br />
watch the raid wipe because your tank on Tallon Zek falls under the<br />
world for 20k damage, and then aggro cannot be gotten by anyone else,<br />
is just more frustrating than I can explain.<br />
<br />
Yes, the raiding content needs to be fixed, but like everyone has<br />
stated, that is just a small portion of the EQ population. There are a<br />
ton of other things that could be, and should be done. If there was a<br />
conceivable way to do a little of each whenever they did updates, that<br />
would be ideal.<br />
<br />
If those really are the top ten things they plan on looking into, they<br />
really have lost touch with the general population of the game and<br />
they should start saying their goodbyes now to many, many people.<br />
<br />
Jenalle Diterra<br />
65 Druid<br />
Titans of Saryrn<br />
Saryrn Server<br />
